title.narrative: Feed the Future Tajikistan Health and Nutrition Activity

description.narrative: (Tajikistan): Optimal health and nutrition are fundamental to achieve USAID's wider mission to end extreme poverty and promote resilient, democratic societies while advancing US national security and prosperity. USAID's Feed the Future (FTF) Tajikistan Health and Nutrition Activity focuses on improving integrated healthcare at the family, community, clinical and national levels to promote maternal, newborn, and child health, including nutrition, sanitation, and hygiene in Tajikistan's FTF geographic focus area. The activity has a four-pronged approach to achieve high-level results focusing on quality of health care, dietary diversity, behavior change, and policy. FY 2018 funds will provide community- and facility- based interventions such as community-based health and nutrition education; hygiene and sanitation; and the promotion of increased access and use of life-saving health intervention provided through a network of local clinical facilities, village organizations and volunteer health educators. Improved access to health care services at the village level leads to stronger more resilient communities more able to support Tajikistan on the pathway to self reliance. Activities align with USG FTF initiatives and foster regional stability by strengthening Tajikistan's sovereignty and independence... .
